Citation.sAbstract: The liquid liquid equilibrium (LLE) properties were measured for the ternary systems ofwater + methanol + dimethyl adipate,water + adipic acid  monomethyl ester + dimethyl adipate andwater + methanol + dimethyl glutarate at temperatures ranging from 298.15 to 318.15Kunder atmospheric  pressure. Each ternary system exhibited type-I LLE behavior and the region of heterogeneity was found to increase with a decrease of temperature.  These new LLE data were correlated with the NRTL model and also used to examine the validity of various versions of the UNIFAC models.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid liquid equilibria of aqueous mixtures containing selected dibasic esters and/or methanol
